**AURA PROJECT DEVELOPMENT PLAN**  
**STAGE-I**

*PROJECT INTRODUCTION***:**

A system that reminds users (students) what are the tasks that they are supposed to complete in that particular week and motivates them to do so by showing how much other people have done it so far. Furthermore, a point system called â€˜Auraâ€™ is used to motivate students to complete their assigned tasks in time.

Furthermore, the system provides functionalities to upload study materials like short notes prepared by them, short videos and various kinds of stuff so that other students can refer to them.

These are the functionalities covered in stage-I of the project.

*SYSTEM COMPONENTS:*

USER INTERFACE:  
Originally planning to implement the user interface in a web based approach, which is compatible with both large screens and small screens. In stage-II the interface will also be implemented with a mobile app.

CONTROL SYSTEM:  
Managing part of the system which connects UI with the database and data storage.

DATABASE:  
Stores data which the system depends on. (Such as user authentication details, system state, logs, etc.)

DATA STORAGE:  
Stores user uploaded data online.

USER INTERFACE

Suggested tools: 	React.js (vite build) / [NEXT.js](http://NEXT.js)  
			Vercel / Nelfy / Firebase (for hosting online)  
			Github (version controlling)   
			Github actions (CI/CD)  
			VScode  
As mentioned previously in this stage only the web page with basic functionalities will be implemented. Developers are encouraged to implement the codebase in a scalable manner.

Functionalities:

1. Login page \- as the landing page  
2. Tasks page \- user will be landed in to this page, once logged in  
3. Resources page \- users can refer to the resources uploaded by other users and   contribute by uploading their resources.  
4. Dummy page- Optional (to be helpful when scale at stage \- II)

![][image1]

CONTROL SYSTEM

Suggested tools: 	Spring Boot (JAVA)  
			Git version control (Github)  
			Postman (for testing API connections)  
			Docker (for containerizing)  
			DockerHub (https://hub.docker.com)  
			Azure (for hosting online)  
			

In this stage, tasks assigned to the controller will be simple as the front end requires only a limited number of functionalities. But the implementation should be done in a scalable manner so that the codebase wonâ€™t be messier when new functionalities are added in the next stages of the project.

Functionalities:

* Login authentication process \- \[0\]  
* Send requested data in Tasks page to the front end from the data storage (or in database) \- \[1\]  
* Store user submitted new tasks in the data storage (or in database) \- \[1\]  
* Send requested data in Resources page to the front end from the data storage\[2\]  
* Store user submitted new resources in the data storage (or in database)- \[2\]  
* Aura calculator  (To be implemented in stage \-II)

Note that:

* For \[0\],\[1\] & \[2\] , the developers should choose proper data structures before implementing.   
* Each functionality should be developed separately for loose coupling.  
* The developer who starts implementing each functionality may choose a proper design pattern.   
* Developers are kindly asked not to use ai-generated codes as the debugging process and scaling process will be quite hard if they do so. And the outcome might be different than the original idea. 




DATABASE

Suggested tools: 	MongoDB atlas  
			Postman (for testing)

Note:  
We will get only a limited storage of 500MB in the free service. We should use that space safely. (Eg: if we use 10MB per day, we will run out of our database storage in  50 days, which is less than a semester)  
We should try to use data storage as much as possible.

DATA STORAGE

Suggested tools: Dropbox / Google drive

Note:  
We can use these cloud services as our storage, as they provide free apiâ€™s for that task. (I used dropbox in my telegram bot project (which could easily be implemented with mongodb, but i decided to go with dropbox for fun ðŸ˜ª (I will put the link below)))  
All the resources will be stored here. Implementing this feature may be a bit more complex than the tasks list.

The developers should choose proper data structures because we need to store data automatically and dont need them to be jumbled when the system matures.
